course = Course(self.xml_math20)
assert course.year == '2017-2018'
assert course.subject == 'MATH'
assert course.code == '20'
assert course.title == 'Calculus'
assert course.description == 'The definite integral, Riemann sums, antiderivatives, the Fundamental Theorem of Calculus, and the Mean Value Theorem for integrals. Integration by substitution and by parts. Area between curves, and volume by slices, washers, and shells. Initial-value problems, exponential and logistic models, direction fields, and parametric curves. Prerequisite: Math 19 or equivalent. If you have not previously taken a calculus course at Stanford then you must have taken the math placement diagnostic (offered through the Math Department website) in order to register for this course.'
assert course.gers == ('GER:DB-Math', 'WAY-FR')
assert course.repeatable == False
assert course.grading_basis == 'Letter or Credit/No Credit'
assert course.units_min == 3
assert course.units_max == 3
assert len(course.objectives) == 1
assert course.final_exam == True
assert len(course.sections) == 8
assert len(course.tags) == 12
assert len(course.attributes) == 3
assert course.course_id == 117229
assert course.active == True
assert course.offer_num == '1'
assert course.academic_group == 'HS'
assert course.academic_org == 'MATH'
assert course.academic_career == 'UG'
assert course.max_units_repeat == 3
assert course.max_times_repeat == 1
